Parameter: intellect
Definition: How effectively the character solves cognitive challenges in their domain — tactical, scientific, creative, social, or any other. Judge by the magnitude of cognitive ability, not the type. A military genius and a scientific genius are measured on the same axis.

Tier calibration (pseudo-characters as lower boundaries):
[T1]  A person with below-average intelligence who regularly misses obvious things.
[T2]  A person of average intelligence with no notable cognitive advantage.
[T3]  A person who is slightly above average — notices what others miss, learns faster.
[T4]  A smart person who solves complex problems with strong analytical ability.
[T5]  An exceptional thinker — expert or strategist who outperforms the vast majority.
[T6]  A genius — among the smartest in their universe within their domain.
[T7]  A transcendent mind that solves problems incomprehensible to others.
[T8]  A being that perceives or processes information beyond mortal comprehension.
[T9]  A being with total omniscience — knows everything, sees all timelines simultaneously.

Return JSON:
{"universe": "{{ universe }}", "parameter": "intellect", "sorted": ["T1", ..., "T9"], "unknown": [...]}

All 9 markers T1..T9 must appear in sorted, in order.

